Articles.Content:
The game is not playable for me. Again.

 

The start menu cannot be pressed. The previous fix does not work anymore.

No mods. Nope. Seems to be stuck to some invisible popup window.

 

Why? Why 1.0.5 still work like charm with any mod i can imagine and a clean 1.1.2 even doesn't respond to mouse clicks? :-/

JohnFX, *shocked*

i have a dual screen setting too.

 

 

I have mentioned my case before: it's the tablet input. The game became incompatible with tablets. 99% of people prefer mice so the problem doesnt arise but it's still here.

 

KSP 1.1.2  works like 1.0.5 when switched to "mouse" mode (completely unacceptable for a tablet user) but stops responding completely in a absolute coordinate mode.


The menu items and lists ARE highlited  but cannot be pressed.

 

There is another severe error in graphics porgramming: when switched to windowed mode the game window is centered across the entire desktop, not an active D3D surface.

 

Practically it means  splitting and syncing D3D output between Intel and Nvidia Surprisingly it works.

 

P.S. It had to turn the "Handwrite input" off for KSP app and the problem temporarily gone. At least for 1.1.2.


It was the same Screen Mapping tab as in my previous report.

 

For a reason but only Schroedinger knows why  KSP and/or Unity now acts like a text input box for Windows! Thus effecively blocking any tablet clicks to menu area.


It drives me crazy so i'm gonna sleep now.

output_log.txt from dxdiag would never diagnose a problem because it does not contain any info on handwriting modules installed into Windows 7 and has no info on tablet mode.
